    "content": "<h2>Sunday Venture Studio Memo</h2><p>🎯 战略雷达 - 2026-04-21</p><p>多轮LLM对话漂移监测：基于Token统计的可靠性新方法 | 92/100 | Strategic Radar</p><p>🏷️ 标签：Long-horizon Agent / 工程基础设施 / 非共识弱信号</p><p>一句判断：\n监测LLM对话一致性，提升Agent可靠性。</p><p>为什么现在：\n解决了多轮LLM交互中“对话漂移”的检测难题，为Agent的长期可靠性提供了关键的实时观测工具。</p><p>非共识视角：\n多数LLM评测关注单轮语义质量，而该研究强调多轮对话的结构一致性，并提出无需模型内部访问的轻量级监测方法，这对于Agent的生产环境部署和长期稳定性至关重要。</p><p>破局点：\n提出的Bipredictability指标和Information Digital Twin架构，通过纯token统计实现100%的矛盾、话题转移检测，为Agent的实时观测和自我修正提供了高效、可扩展的机制。</p><p>行动建议：\n工程团队：在未来2周内，研究该论文的IDT架构，评估其在现有Agent对话系统中的集成可行性，并规划概念验证，用于实时监测对话一致性。</p><p>入选理由：\n该论文提出Bipredictability指标和Information Digital Twin架构，通过token频率统计直接监测对话结构一致性，无需嵌入或模型内部访问，100%检测出矛盾、话题转移等问题。这直接影响Long-horizon Agent的可靠性、评测和观测，是新的评测和观测方法，具有高行动可执行性。</p><h2>Source Context</h2><p>arXiv:2604.13061v2 Announce Type: replace-cross Abstract: Large language models, LLMs, are increasingly deployed in multiturn settings where earlier responses shape later ones, making reliability dependent on whether a conversation remains consistent over time. When this consistency degrades undetected, downstream decisions lose their grounding in the exchange that produced them. Yet current evaluation methods assess isolated outputs rather than the interaction producing them. Here we show that conversational structural consistency can be monitored directly from token frequency statistics, without embeddings, auxiliary evaluators or access to model internals. We formalize this signal as Bipredictability, P, which measures shared predictability across the context, response, next prompt loop relative to the turn total uncertainty, and implement it in a lightweight auxiliary architecture,...</p>",
