    "content": "<h2>Sunday Venture Studio Memo</h2><p>🎯 战略雷达 - 2026-04-21</p><p>对抗环境下的安全约束强化学习：Agent可靠性新突破 | 92/100 | Strategic Radar</p><p>🏷️ 标签：Long-horizon Agent / 模型与架构 / 非共识弱信号</p><p>一句判断：\nAgent在对抗中学习，确保安全和最优。</p><p>为什么现在：\n解决了Agent在真实世界部署中，面对外部不确定性和对抗时的安全性和可靠性问题，是Agent落地关键。</p><p>非共识视角：\n传统RL多假设环境稳定，而该研究明确将外部因素建模为“悲观对手”，并提供理论安全保证，这对于Agent在高风险、高不确定性场景的部署具有颠覆性意义。</p><p>破局点：\n提出的RHC-UCRL算法，通过对Agent和对手策略的乐观维护，在理论上保证了次线性遗憾和约束违反，为构建可信赖的Agent系统提供了坚实基础。</p><p>行动建议：\n研究团队：在未来2周内，深入研究RHC-UCRL算法，评估其在自动驾驶或金融交易Agent等安全关键场景中的应用潜力，并规划概念验证。</p><p>入选理由：\n该研究首次在明确对抗动态下研究安全约束RL，提出RHC-UCRL算法，通过对Agent和对手策略的乐观维护，实现次线性遗憾和约束违反保证。这直接影响Long-horizon Agent的可靠性和安全性，是新架构和新训练方法，具有高行动可执行性。</p><h2>Source Context</h2><p>arXiv:2604.14243v2 Announce Type: replace-cross Abstract: Real-world decision-making systems operate in environments where state transitions depend not only on the agent&#x27;s actions, but also on \\textbf{exogenous factors outside its control}--competing agents, environmental disturbances, or strategic adversaries--formally, $s_{h+1} = f(s_h, a_h, \\bar{a}_h)+\\omega_h$ where $\\bar{a}_h$ is the adversary/external action, $a_h$ is the agent&#x27;s action, and $\\omega_h$ is an additive noise. Ignoring such factors can yield policies that are optimal in isolation but \\textbf{fail catastrophically in deployment}, particularly when safety constraints must be satisfied. Standard Constrained MDP formulations assume the agent is the sole driver of state evolution, an assumption that breaks down in safety-critical settings. Existing robust RL approaches address this via distributional robustness over trans...</p>",
